suites.title: JavaScript Array Demonstration - FSM & UI validation

specs.title: No unexpected console errors or runtime exceptions occurred during interactions
Initial render shows the default array, length, and output placeholder
Add to End (push) appends item and updates UI & output
Add to Start (unshift) inserts at beginning and clears input
Remove from End (pop) removes last item and updates output
Remove from Start (shift) removes first item and updates output
Removing from empty array triggers alert "Array is empty!"

suites.title: Other common methods: sort, reverse, find, filter, map, reset

specs.title: Sort sorts alphabetically and updates the display & output
Reverse reverses order and updates the display & output
Find "Apple" finds the item (case-insensitive) and reports result
Filter items > length 5 returns expected list and does not modify original array
Map items converts to uppercase and updates the array & output
Reset returns array to initial values after modifications
Attempting to add an empty value triggers alert and does not change array
Multiple operations in sequence produce expected combined effects
